The Board consists of the following voting members:
One representative of each of the 4-year institutions of higher education offering a Commission-approved program at the Center and at a site, appointed by the institution; and
The following 10 representatives, appointed in accordance with the bylaws of the Board:
Three representatives of regional businesses, industries, or corporations;
One representative of the Cecil County Office of Economic Development;
One representative of the Harford County Office of Economic Development;
One representative of Cecil College;
One representative of Harford Community College;
One representative of the Northeast Maryland University Research Park; and
Two representatives chosen from the community at large.
